- *Lemborexant/DORA tau neuroprotection integration* ([Chapter 15, new speculation @spec:ch15-orexin-pka-tau (cert 0.25) on orexin→PKA→tau phosphorylation as a production-prevention mechanism distinct from glymphatic clearance, plus new "Pharmacological Convergences on the cAMP/PKA Tau Phosphorylation Axis" section covering DORA class comparison, propranolol PKA dampening, prazosin unresolved tension, lithium/GSK3β, valproate/HDAC+GSK3β, and the central paradox of suppressing already-low orexin in ME/CFS; Chapter 14b, DORA neuroprotection note added to daridorexant section; zolpidem glymphatic warning strengthened with Parhizkar null-finding (zolpidem increased sleep but gave zero tau protection); references.bib, 3 new entries (@Parhizkar2025LemborexantTau cert 0.85, @Lucey2023SuvorexantTau cert 0.75, @Kang2009OrexinAmyloid cert 0.95); Appendix H, new section `sec:bib-lemborexant-dora-tau` with 3 annotated entries; hypothesis registry, 1 new entry; content-staging/literature-lemborexant-dora-tau-2026-05-28.md, Phase 1 literature review; content-staging/brainstorm-lemborexant-dora-tau-2026-05-28.md, Phase 3 brainstorm (70 ideas); ops/plans/lemborexant-dora-tau-integration-plan.md, new plan]): Parhizkar et al. (2025, Nature Neuroscience) demonstrated that lemborexant (DORA) reduces tau phosphorylation via PKA pathway inhibition (orexin→cAMP→PKA→tau p), preventing neurodegeneration (30--40% hippocampal volume preservation) in tauopathy mice — while zolpidem increased sleep but provided zero neuroprotection, proving orexin signaling (not sleep duration) drives the effect. Lucey et al. (2023) provided human validation in an RCT (n=38): suvorexant 20 mg reduced CSF p-tau181/T181 by ~10--15%. Three pharmacologically distinct strategies now form a ladder: production prevention (DORAs→PKA), clearance enhancement (glymphatic), and damage reversal (HSP70 exosomes). Medication connections explored: propranolol via β-adrenergic→cAMP→PKA convergence, prazosin's unresolved tension