 HIF isoform rebalancing, TGF-beta1 blockade; Chapter 19, 3 new integrative protocols: dual mast cell-MMP inhibition, timed collagen cofactor protocol, CCI multi-modal management; Chapter 20, 6 new biomarker speculations in "Connective Tissue and ECM Biomarkers" section; Chapter 25b, 4 new proposed studies; Chapter 27, 2 math model proposals; Chapter 28, mast cell-ECM bistable model; Chapter 30, multi-compartment ECM turnover model + HIF-1alpha-Mito-ECM triad cross-ref; Chapter 31, ECM degradation temporal trajectory speculation; Chapter 32, sigmoid CCI-orthostatic model; hypothesis-registry.typ, 48 new entries; hypotheses-trees/subtrees/new-contents-connective-tissue.md, populated from stub with 60 nodes; hypotheses-trees/hypotheses-trees.md, updated root index; ops/plans/connective-tissue-disorders-integration-plan.md, new plan]): Comprehensive expansion of prior limited CTD integration — all 64 brainstorm ideas now integrated across 20 chapter files. Core framework: HIF-1alpha-mitochondria-ECM self-reinforcing triad as unifying mechanism producing connective tissue pathology, mast cell-MMP positive feedback creating bistable degraded states, basement membrane thickening impairing both perfusion and glymphatic clearance, and structural-vs-functional orthostatic intolerance stratification for treatment selection. Key additions: post-exertional MMP surge as PEM amplifier, glymphatic-capillary bidirectional impairment, circadian collagen synthesis optimization, CCI progressive overload pacing protocol, multi-compartment ECM turnover model, sigmoid CCI-orthostatic severity model. Prior changelog entry (May 13) covered only 2 hypotheses + 10 papers; this pass completes the full pipeline for the topic. _Motivated by:_ @Wirth2026CTDMECFS — bidirectional CTD-ME/CFS relationship proposing ROS-prolyl hydroxylase-HIF-1alpha-mast cell pathway; @Moschini2026HIFTendinopathy — HIF-1alpha drives connective tissue pathology independently of VEGF; @Wust2024capillary — capillary bas