- *Exercise recovery and PEM duration integration* ([Chapter 2, PEM measurement section updated; Chapter 5, severity levels section updated; Chapter 14a, core mechanisms section updated with epigenetic/EV hypotheses; Chapter 14d, cross-disease section updated with Long COVID comparison; Chapter 14f, CPET-derived section updated; Chapter 25b, proposed studies section updated; Appendix H, 11 new annotated entries; references.bib, 19 new entries; hypothesis-registry.typ, 6 new entries]): Comprehensive integration of 20-paper literature review on 2-day CPET, PEM recovery duration, and exercise testing in ME/CFS. Updated PEM measurement section with largest 2-day CPET study (Keller2024CPET), ICF discrimination evidence, and 24h interval limitation. Added severity vs PEM recovery patterns analysis with severity-independent PEM mechanism speculation. Added CPET-2 deterioration as ME/CFS-specific signature hypothesis. Added Long COVID vs ME/CFS PEM divergence hypothesis (null result from Gattoni2025LongCOVIDCPET). Added novel mechanistic insights: prolonged epigenetic recovery hypothesis (Sharma2025EpigeneticPEM) and EV-mediated intercellular signaling speculation (Giloteaux2024EVExercise). Added comprehensive multi-timepoint PEM recovery duration study proposal to Ch25b. Updated hypothesis registry with 6 new entries (3 hypotheses, 2 speculations, 1 study). _Motivated by:_  — largest 2-day CPET study confirming Day 2 deterioration; @vanCampen2020SeverityCPET — severity patterns in 2-day CPET;  — 48h epigenetic changes post-exercise;  — EV proteome changes with exercise;  — Long COVID null result showing no CPET-2 impairment.

